[h1][b]Stellaris [v4.2] Error Janitor[/b][/h1]
[h3][b]Because someone had to.[/b][/h3]
[p]This is a continuation of [URL=steamcommunity.com/workshop/filedetails/3013030800]Vanilla Fixes v3.11.x[/URL] by [URL=steamcommunity.com/id/renegades-modding-group]RMG[/URL] and even more, it combines some old Vanilla Fixes mods that I found (credits below and in-code).[/p]
[hr]
I initially created these fixes for myself to eliminate the noise and give myself a foundation for actually modding in peace. Since it's well known that PDX sometimes never fixes certain bugs[spoiler]or only fixes them years later[/spoiler]. So, I've now started releasing this collection of general bug fixes for Vanilla[spoiler] and to give Stellaris a little kick in the bottom[/spoiler].
The plan is to make the mod timeless and to continuously expand and update it. All bug fixes included in all [i]my other mods[/i] will be slowly integrated here.

[h2][b]What This Does[/b][/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Fixes "Features":[/b] Corrects a huge amount of various bugs I or other found.
[*][b]Performance:[/b] tuning, script logic, cleanups (merging) AI_weights and modifiers, using modern syntax as intended, sorting triggers after priority.
[*][b]Localisation:[/b] some open reported fixes (for all languages).
[*][b]Creates a Base for Modding:[/b] Lets you build on a foundation that isn't actively screaming at you.
[*][b]Silences the [i]error.log[/i]:[/b] Fixes spam so you can find *real* errors (like from your other mods).
[/list]
Creating these bug fixes is a lot of work, but listing and documenting them is another level of effort. Therefore, due to the sheer amount, each bug is usually self-explanatory in the code and marked with "[b]# Vfix[/b]" (~1000â€“even not counting minor ones).
[p]A detailed list of fixes will follow soon[spoiler]â€“possible, since PDS will integrate the majority of these fixes into the next version, it's maybe not needed[/spoiler].[/p]

